### Description

As per the docs (https://angular.io/guide/defer#triggers) the syntax or the `@defer when` is:

```
@defer (when cond) {
  <calendar-cmp />
}
```

But the below code doesnt work:

```
@defer (when (emailConfirmed && !resumeExists))
{
<app-dialog disableClose="true">
......
</app-dialog>
}
```

Whereas this works perfectly fine:

Component:
```
  isVisible() {
    return (this.emailConfirmed && !this.resumeExists);
  }

```

Template:
```
@defer (when isVisible()){
{
<app-dialog disableClose="true">
......
</app-dialog>
}

```


### Please provide a link to a minimal reproduction of the bug

The above code added in any component should reproduce same behavior

